  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The aim of this experimental study was to test the effect of increasing dietary calcium
      intake to 1500 mg/day on increases in bone quality in adolescent females. The hypothesis to
      be tested is: adolescent females who consume a high calcium diet will have a greater increase
      in bone quality, as measured by densitometry and ultrasound, than adolescent females who
      consume their usual dietary calcium intake.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
